Ervin
=====

Installing
----------

Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~

Django 1.0 or later. Not tested with Django 1.1 (soon!)

Noid. http://search.cpan.org/dist/Noid/

Solr & solango, for search.

Django atompub, for feeds.

All requirements are installed in the following steps.

Steps
~~~~~

::

 $ sudo perl -MCPAN -e "install Noid" # change sudo for your platform as necessary

 $ mkdir my_project

 $ cd my_project

 $ mkdir code

 $ cd code

 $ bzr co https://code.launchpad.net/~ehetzner/ervin/trunk ervin

 $ wget http://www.djangoproject.com/download/1.0.3/tarball/

 $ tar xzvf Django-1.0.3.tar.gz

 $ cd Django-1.0.3

 $ patch -p0 <../ervin/django_1.0.3.diff

 $ cd ..
 
 $ svn co http://django-atompub.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ django-atompub

 $ cd .. # that is, to my_project

 $ ln -s code/ervin/ervin ervin

 $ ln -s code/Django-1.0.3/django django

 $ ln -s code/django-atompub/atompub/ atompub

 $ export PYTHONPATH=`pwd` # use equivalent in (t)csh

 $ python django/bin/django-admin.py startproject my_project

 $ cd my_project

 $ noid dbcreate .reeeeek

Use your editor to configure the database in ``settings.py``. Add
``ervin`` and ``django.contrib.admin`` to ``INSTALLED_APPS``, e.g.::

 INSTALLED_APPS = (
     'django.contrib.auth',
     'django.contrib.admin',
     'django.contrib.contenttypes',
     'django.contrib.sessions',
     'django.contrib.sites',
     'ervin'
 )

Edit ``urls.py`` appropriately. For instance::

 from django.contrib import admin
 admin.autodiscover()

 urlpatterns = patterns('',
     (r'^admin/(.*)', admin.site.root),
     (r'', include('ervin.urls')),
 )

::

 $ python manage.py syncdb

 $ python manage.py runserver

Visit http://localhost:8000/admin and begin adding data!